annotationA: Putative ATP-dependent RNA helicase me31b; Unwinds RNA in an ATP-dependent fashion (Potential). Involved in germ cell formation
annotationB: Maternal protein exuperantia; Ensures the proper localization of the mRNA of the bicoid gene to the anterior regions of the oocyte thus playing a fundamental role in the establishment of the polarity of the oocyte. May bind the bcd mRNA
